description:
Given an integer n, return all the numbers in the range [1, n] sorted in lexicographical order.

### Example 1

### Input

```CPP
n=13
```

### Output

```CPP
[1,10,11,12,13,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9]
```

### Example 2

### Input

```CPP
n=2
```

### Output

```CPP
[1,2]
```

### Constraints:

- 1 <= n <= 5 \* 10^4
title: Arrengement
